uardian%20to%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Space%20Force%20is%20sending%20its%20first%20member%20%E2%80%94%20which%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3BGuardians%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSSF%20Col.%20Nick%20Hague%20is%20set%20to%20pilot%20a%20NASA%20mission%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20as%20early%20as%20August%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spaceforce.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3662607%2Fspace-force-guardian-set-to-launch-to-international-space-station-on-nasa-missi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpace%20Force%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20NASA%20astronauts%20and%20a%20Russian%20cosmonaut%20will%20join%20the%20Crew-9%20mission%20aboard%20the%20Dragon%2C%20a%20Space%20X%20spacecraft.%20Upon%20arrival%20at%20the%20ISS%2C%20Hague%20will%20pivot%20to%20serving%20as%20a%20flight%20engineer.%20The%20crew%20%26quot%3Bwill%20conduct%20a%20wide-ranging%20set%20of%20operations%20and%20research%20activities%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20their%20more%20than%20six-month%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20USSF%20press%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20core%20of%20our%20mission%20on%20the%20space%20station%20is%20to%20perform%20science%20experiments%20and%20collect%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Hague%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BThe%20International%20Space%20Station%20provides%20a%20unique%20platform%20in%20microgravity%2C%20which%20allows%20researchers%20from%20around%20the%20world%20to%20explore%20and%20discover%20processes%20that%20could%20have%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20behavior%20of%20our%20bodies%20and%20the%20environment%20around%20us%20both%20on%20Earth%20and%20off%20planet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Space%20Force%20is%20only%20four%20years%20old%20%E2%80%94%20the%20baby%20among%20long-standing%20US%20military%20branches%20like%20the%20US%20Army%2C%20US%20Marine%20Corps%2C%20US%20Navy%2C%20US%20Air%20Force%2C%20US