20Sixth%20Schedule%20are%20being%20subject%20to%20harassment.%20Now%20there%20are%20lobbies%20in%20the%20mining%20industry%20who%20want%20to%20destroy%20Ladakh.%20We%20are%20only%20demanding%20our%20constitutional%20rights%20and%20we%20will%20not%20rest%20until%20it%20happens%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wangchuk%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgovernment%2Fladakhs-people-wary-of-development-seven-months-after-article-370-read-down%2F%5C%22%3ELadakh%E2%80%99s%20People%20Wary%20of%20%E2%80%98Development%E2%80%99%20Seven%20Months%20After%20Article%20370%20Read-Down%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20education%20reformer%20and%20climate%20change%20activist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fladakhi-innovator-sonam-wangchuk-says-hes-under-house-arrest-police-deny-charge%2Farticle66445976.ece%5C%22%3Ewas%20placed%20under%20house%20arrest%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%2C%20following%20a%20five-day%20fast%20in%20support%20of%20protection%20of%20Ladakh%20under%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule.%20The%20Ladakh%20police%20had%2C%20however%2C%20denied%20the%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESyed%20Zafar%20Mehdi%2C%20a%20trader%2C%20said%20that%20he%20had%20come%20all%20the%20way%20from%20Turtuk%2C%20the%20last%20village%20on%20the%20border%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20demonstration.%20%E2%80%9CI%20understand%20the%20importance%20of%20issues%20such%20as%20Sixth%20Schedule%20and%20statehood%20because%20our%20community%20lives%20in%20front%20of%20the%20enemy.%20I%20fully%20support%20the%20demands%20of%20LAB%20and%20KDA%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20the%20protesters%20took%20out%20a%20march%20from%20Sengge%20Namgyal%20square%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Leh%20to%20the%20deputy%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20covering%20a%20distance%20of%20about%20two%20kilometres.%20Throughout%20the%20march%2C%20they%20continued%20to%20chant%20slogans%20while%20displaying%20placards%20advocating%20for%20statehood%2C%20inclusion%20in%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%2C%20and%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20demonstration%20was%20held%20in%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20Kargil%20district.%20This%20protest%20was%20also%20attended%20by%20thousands%20of%20people.%20The%20demonstrators%20chanted%20slogans%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%20and%20reservation%20in%20jobs%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESlogans%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Nahin%20chalegi%2C%20nahin%20chalegi%2C%20nainsaafi%20nahin%20chalegi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Injustice%20won%E2%80%99t%20work)%E2%80%99%20and%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Ladakh%20kay%20tribal%20status%20ko%2C%20nafiz%20karo%20nafiz%20karo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(pronounce%20tribal%20status%20for%20Ladakh)%E2%80%99%20echoed%20during%20the%20demonstration%20in%20Kargil%20district%20on%20Saturday.%20Some%20demonstrators%20were%20carrying%20placards%20which%20read%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20demand%20statehood.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChering%20Dorjay%2C%20one%20of%20the%20members%20of%20LBA%20and%20a%20former%20J%26amp%3BK%20minister%2C%20said%20that%20the%20outpouring%20of%20support%20for%20the%20shutdown%20call%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cclear%20message%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20that%20it%20should%20concede%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20demanding%20anything%20extra-constitutional.%20Tribal%20status%20is%20the%20right%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Ladakh.%20The%20Centre%20should%20respect%20our%20sentiments%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dorjay%2C%20who%20resigned%20as%20the%20chief%20of%20Ladakh%20BJP%20in%202020%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%204%2C%20a%20committee%20formed%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%20had%20held%20the%20first%20round%20of%20talks%20with%20the%20leaders%20of%20LAB%20and%20KDA%2C%20without%20any%20significant%20breakthrough.%20While%20the%20committee%20had%20discussed%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20safeguards%E2%80%9D%20for%20Ladakh%20during%20the%20meeting%2C%20the%20LAB%20and%20KDA%20have%20stuck%20to%20their%20four%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20round%20of%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20sides%20is%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20on%20February%2019%20in%20Delhi%2C%20according%20to%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELadakh%20was%20separated%20from%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20downgraded%20into%20a%20Union%20Territory%20without%20a%20legislature%20in%202019%2C%20when%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20read%20down%20Article%20370%2C%20sparking%20concerns%20of%20political%20and%20economic%20disempowerment%20in%20the%20arid%20desert%20region%20bordering%20China%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706964359000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03180459%2Fimage-1809.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwe-demand-statehood-shutdown-in-ladakh-as-protesters-call-for-inclusion-in-sixth-schedule%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20shutdown%20was%20observed%20in%20Leh%20and%20Kargil%20districts%2C%20as%20businesses%20suspended%20their%20daily%20activities%2C%20even%20in%20the%20remote%20Zanskar%20and%20Nubra%20Valley%20regions%2C%20while%20public%20transport%20largely%20remained%20off%20the%20roads.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwe-demand-statehood-shutdown-in-ladakh-as-protesters-call-for-inclusion-in-sixth-schedule%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Canadian%20Intelligence%20Said%20India%20Involved%20in%20%E2%80%98Foreign%20Interference%E2%80%99%20Activities%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19221735%2Fcanadian-flag-1229484_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20inquiry%20into%20foreign%20interference%20in%20its%20last%20two%20federal%20elections%20has%20named%20India%20and%20China%20and%20called%20for%20Ottawa%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20more%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20a%20top%20secret%20briefing%20report%20obtained%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalnews.ca%2Fnews%2F10264872%2Fcanada-china-foreign-interference-elections-csis-report%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20News%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20declassified%20document%2C%20dated%20February%2024%2C%202023%20and%20titled%20%E2%80%9CBriefing%20to%20the%20Minister%20of%20Democratic%20Institutions%20on%20Foreign%20Interference%E2%80%9D%2C%20has%20called%20China%20%E2%80%9Cby%20far%20the%20most%20significant%20threat%E2%80%9D%20while%20also%20naming%20India%20as%20a%20foreign%20interference%20threat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20outlet%20quoted%20the%20report%20as%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20must%20do%20more%20to%20protect%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20robust%20democratic%20institutions%20and%20processes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20News%20said%20that%20the%20briefing%20report%20was%20released%20to%20it%20under%20the%20Access%20to%20Information%20Act%20as%20a%20commission%20of%20inquiry%20into%20foreign%20interference%20in%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20recent%20elections%20got%20underway%20in%20Ottawa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20wrapped%20up%20its%20first%20set%20of%20hearings%20on%20Friday%20(February%202).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20intelligence%20report%20devoted%20almost%20three%20pages%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%2C%20the%20excerpts%20were%20entirely%20redacted%20except%20for%20a%20single%20sentence%20that%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20engages%20in%20FI%20%5Bforeign%20interference%5D%20activities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20the%20only%20country%20identified%20by%20name%20aside%20from%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20month%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadas-probe-panel-to-examine-indias-alleged-role-in-the-last-two-federal-elections%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20a%20statement%20by%20the%20foreign%20interference%20commission%20as%20saying%20it%20had%20requested%20the%20Canadian%20government%20to%20provide%20information%20related%20to%20alleged%20interference%20the%20Indian%20government%20in%20Canadian%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPursuant%20to%20its%20Terms%20of%20Reference%2C%20the%20Foreign%20Interference%20Commission%20has%20requested%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20collection%20and%20production%20of%20document%20relating%20to%20paragraphs%20clause%20(a)(i)(A)%20and%20(a)(i)(B)%20of%20its%20Terms%20of%20Reference%20include%20information%20and%20documents%20relating%20to%20alleged%20interference%20by%20India%20related%20to%20the%202019%20and%202021%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20briefing%20report%20accessed%20by%20Global%20News%20states%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20extent%20of%20foreign%20interference%20in%20Canada%20is%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%2C%20pervasive%20and%20directed%20against%20all%20levels%20of%20government%20and%20civil%20society%20all%20across%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20has%20called%20for%20%E2%80%9Cclearly%20articulated%20strategies%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20raising%20awareness%20and%20briefing%20officials%20and%20politicians%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccentral%20to%20these%20efforts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%20that%20all%20government%20agencies%20must%20work%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdetect%2C%20disrupt%20and%20publicise%E2%80%9D%20interference.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20responsibility%20to%20counter%20these%20harmful%20activities%20must%20be%20shared%20across%20government%2C%20including%20provincial%20and%20municipal%20partners%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20commission%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.canada.ca%2Fen%2Fdemocratic-institutions%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2Fgovernment-of-canada-launches-public-inquiry-into-foreign-interference.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elaunched%20in%20September%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20explicitly%20mentioned%20that%20it%20would%20examine%20interference%20in%20Canadian%20elections%20by%20China%2C%20Russia%20and%20unnamed%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20actors%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20its%20functioning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20according%20to%20last%20month%E2%80%99s%20press%20release%2C%20the%20commission%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20potential%20role%20was%20also%20being%20examined.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20intelligence%20briefing%20report%2C%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20in%20September%20publicly%20accused%20India%20of%20being%20behind%20the%20shooting%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20who%20was%20proscribed%20as%20a%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20by%20Indian%20security%20agencies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubsequently%2C%20New%20Democratic%20Party%20leader%20Jagmeet%20Singh%2C%20an%20ally%20of%20the%20Trudeau%20government%2C%20had%20written%20to%20the%20commission%20to%20look%20into%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20having%20influenced%20elections%20through%20its%20large%20diaspora.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20on%20its%20part%20had%20denied%20the%20accusation%2C%20with%20both%20countries%20expelling%20a%20diplomat%20each.%20India%20had%20also%20stopped%20visa%20services%20for%20Canadian%20nationals%2C%20which%20it%20resumed%20after%20about%20a%20month.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20Delhi%20also%20asked%20Canada%20to%20cut%20down%20its%20diplomatic%20presence%20so%20that%20there%20is%20parity%2C%20which%20led%20Ottawa%20to%20withdraw%20over%2040%20diplomats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubsequently%2C%C2%A0US%20federal%20prosecutors%20announced%20in%20November%20that%20there%20was%20a%20possible%20link%20between%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%20and%20the%20foiling%20of%20an%20alleged%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20Canadian-American%20Khalistan%20supporter%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Global%20News%2C%20the%20Feburary%202023%20intelligence%20report%20also%20called%20for%20%E2%80%9Cdecisive%20action%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20imposition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconsequences%20on%20perpetrators%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CUltimately%2C%20better%20protecting%20Canadian%20democratic%20institutions%20against%20FI%20will%20require%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20and%20a%20willingness%20to%20take%20decisive%20action%20and%20impose%20consequences%20on%20perpetrators%2C%E2%80%9D%20Global%20News%20quoted%20the%20briefing%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CUntil%20FI%20is%20viewed%20as%20constituting%20an%20existential%20threat%20to%20Canadian%20democracy%20and%20the%20government%20forcefully%20and%20actively%20responds%2C%20these%20threats%20will%20persist.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706963120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F19221735%2Fcanadian-flag-1229484_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanada-intelligence-india-foreign-inteference-global-news%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20report%20devoted%20almost%20three%20pages%20to%20India's%20role%2C%20the%20excerpts%20were%20entirely%20redacted%20except%20for%20a%20single%20sentence%20that%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20engages%20in%20FI%20%5Bforeign%20interference%5D%20activities.%E2%80%9D%20India%20is%20the%20only%20country%20identified%20by%20name%20aside%20from%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanada-intelligence-india-foreign-inteference-global-news%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Goodluck%20Q3%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20grows%2072%25%20to%20Rs%2032%20crore%2C%20income%20up%2024%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706962313000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-02%2F19%2Ffull%2F1676817940-8267.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgoodluck-q3-results-net-profit-grows-72-to-rs-32-crore-income-up-24-124020300780_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20had%20clocked%20a%20net%20profit%20of%20Rs%2018.40%20crore%20during%20the%20October-December%20period%20of%20preceding%202022-23%20financial%20year%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgoodluck-q3-results-net-profit-grows-72-to-rs-32-crore-income-up-24-124020300780_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgoodluck-q3-results-net-profit-grows-72-to-rs-32-crore-income-up-24-124020300780_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fgoodluck-q3-results-net-profit-grows-72-to-rs-32-crore-income-up-24-124020300780_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20Pakistan%20PM%20Imran%20Khan%20jailed%20again%20-%20this%20time%20for%20breaking%20marriage