government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fpunjab%2Fwill-examine-all-bills-on-merit-says-punjab-guv-as-the-aap-govt-moves-sc-2747104%5C%22%3Emoved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20Purohit%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20following%20which%20the%20apex%20court%20reprimanded%20him%20for%20the%20delay%20in%20giving%20assent%20to%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20top%20court%20bench%20even%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20are%20playing%20with%20fire%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20was%20unhappy%20with%20the%20deadlock%20between%20the%20Punjab%20government%20and%20him.%20AAP%20has%20repeatedly%20maintained%20that%20Purohit%20violated%20established%20constitutional%20traditions%20and%20conventions%20for%20political%20reasons%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20BJP%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPurohit%2C%20a%20senior%20BJP%20member%20from%20Maharashtra%2C%20denied%20these%20allegations%20and%20maintained%20that%20he%20had%20the%20right%20to%20question%20the%20wrongdoings%20of%20the%20state%20government%20in%20the%20larger%20public%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20AAP%20government%20has%20not%20officially%20reacted%20to%20his%20resignation%20yet%2C%20some%20of%20the%20party%20leaders%20have%20called%20it%20%E2%80%98good%20riddance%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20contacted%2C%20AAP%20Punjab%20spokesperson%20Malvinder%20Kang%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20they%20had%20always%20respected%20Purohit%2C%20but%20that%20he%20misused%20the%20sanctity%20of%20his%20office%20in%20creating%20unnecessary%20hurdles%20for%20an%20elected%20government%20at%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20behest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPunjab%20was%20no%20different%20from%20other%20non-BJP%20ruled%20states%20where%20elected%20governments%20were%20harassed%20by%20the%20BJP%20through%20their%20appointees%20in%20the%20governors%E2%80%99%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20one%20can%E2%80%99t%20really%20guess%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20game%20plan%20behind%20Purohit%E2%80%99s%20sudden%20resignation%2C%20it%20appears%20to%20me%20that%20he%20was%20tired%20of%20taking%20orders%20from%20the%20BJP%20against%20the%20AAP%20government%20and%20finally%20released%20himself%20of%20this%20pressure%20by%20resigning%20from%20the%20post%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%20that%20his%20successor%20would%20not%20interfere%20in%20the%20day-to-day%20working%20of%20the%20government%20like%20he%20did%20and%20allow%20the%20constitutionally%20elected%20government%20to%20fulfil%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20mandate.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706960217000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F17174308%2FUntitled-design-2021-09-17T174255.378.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpunjab-governor-banwarilal-purohit-resigns-citing-personal-reasons%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Purohit's%20resignation%20comes%20days%20after%20allegations%20of%20tampering%20in%20the%20Chandigarh%20mayoral%20elections%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20BJP%20candidate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpunjab-governor-banwarilal-purohit-resigns-citing-personal-reasons%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Michael%20Madhusudan%20Dutta%2C%20the%2019th%20century%20Poet%2C%20Essayist%20and%20Iconoclast%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03164144%2Fimage-1807.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CExtensive%20dissemination%20of%20knowledge%20amongst%20women%20is%20the%20surest%20way%20that%20leads%20a%20nation%20to%20civilisation%20and%20refinement%2C%20for%20it%20is%20women%20who%20first%20give%20ideas%20to%20the%20future%20philosopher%20and%20the%20would-be%20poet%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20I%20may%20say%20in%20all%20the%20Oriental%20countries%20women%20are%20looked%20upon%20as%20created%20merely%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20gratification%20of%20the%20animal%20appetites%20of%20men.%20This%20brutal%20misconception%20of%20the%20design%20of%20the%20Almighty%20is%20the%20source%20of%20much%20misery%20to%20the%20fair%20sex%2C%20because%20it%20not%20only%20makes%20them%20appear%20as%20of%20inferior%20mental%20endowments%2C%20but%20no%20better%20than%20a%20sort%20of%20speaking%20brutes.%20The%20people%20of%20this%20country%20do%20not%20know%20the%20pleasure%20of%20domestic%20life%2C%20and%20indeed%20they%20cannot%20know%2C%20until%20civilization%20shows%20them%20the%20way%20to%20attain%20to%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20lines%20from%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4419214%5C%22%3Eessay%3C%2Fa%3E%20written%20by%20a%2019th%20century%20Bengali%20student%20of%20Hindu%20College%2C%20a%20premier%20educational%20institution%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20then%20the%20national%20capital.%20It%20came%20out%20in%201842.%20And%2C%20his%20age%3F%20Eighteen.%20This%20was%20only%20his%20second%20attempt%20to%20be%20published%20in%20this%20period%2C%20the%20first%20one%20being%20a%20criticism%20on%20English%20poetry%20%E2%80%93%20Michael%20Madhusudan%20Dutta%20was%20showing%20his%20writing%20skills%20at%20an%20early%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20former%20one%2C%20here%20also%2C%20the%20young%20lad%20used%20a%20handful%20of%20poetry%20and%20proverbial%20references.%20Given%20his%20tender%20age%20and%20the%20admiration%20he%20held%20for%20classical%20European%20literature%2C%20the%20style%20was%20expected.%20Dutta%E2%80%99s%20English%20poems%20were%20also%20getting%20published%20simultaneously%2C%20in%20some%20of%20the%20leading%20English%20journals.%20His%20message%20was%20direct%20enough%2C%20though%2C%20and%20the%20essay%2C%20with%20no%20distinct%20title%2C%20would%20earn%20him%20a%20gold%20medal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20he%20would%20convert%20to%20Christianity%20within%20a%20year%2C%20only%20to%20avoid%20his%20marriage%20to%20a%20much%20younger%20and%20illiterate%20village%20girl%2C%20arranged%20by%20his%20advocate%20father%2C%20Rajnarayan%20Dutta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20late%201847%2C%20Dutta%20left%20Calcutta%2C%20his%20beloved%20friends%20and%20loving%20mother%2C%20to%20eventually%20settle%20down%20in%20Madras.%20Here%2C%20he%20would%20teach%2C%20edit%20English%20magazines%2C%20marry%20an%20English%20lady%20and%20associate%20with%20organisations%20of%20native%20freethinkers.%20These%20ventures%20in%20a%20city%20completely%20different%20from%20the%20one%20he%20hailed%20from%2C%20gave%20him%20the%20opportunity%20to%20meet%20different%20classes.%20His%20observations%20of%20his%20time%20and%20personal%20struggle%20with%20life%20would%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20lay%20the%20foundation%20of%20a%20literary%20genius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98The%20Captive%20Ladie%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Rizia%20%E2%80%93%20Empress%20of%20Inde%E2%80%99%20are%20the%20two%20major%20works%20that%20came%20out%20during%20his%20stay%20at%20Madras.%20Both%20works%20deal%20with%20two%20significant%20chapters%20of%20Indian%20history.%20The%20central%20theme%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Captive%20Ladie%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20legend%20of%20Prithviraj%20Chauhan%20and%20Sanyogita%20and%20in%20the%20second%2C%20a%20play%2C%20he%20paid%20his%20tribute%20to%20Razia%20Sultan%2C%20the%20only%20female%20Muslim%20ruler%20of%20Delhi%20Sultanate.%20While%20the%20first%20one%20can%20be%20called%20his%20first%20step%20to%20becoming%20a%20poets%E2%80%99%20poet%20of%20Indian%20literature%2C%20the%20latter%20one%20is%20the%20first%20ever%20text%20with%20a%20Muslim%20protagonist%2C%20written%20by%20any%20non-Muslim%20Bengali%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20Even%20though%20wars%20and%20treachery%20constitute%20the%20historical%20background%20of%20the%20central%20story%20in%20both%2C%20Madhusudan%E2%80%99s%20primary%20focus%20was%20on%20a%20more%20important%20aspect%20of%20human%20life%3A%20love.%20Being%20a%20%E2%80%98friendless%20stranger%E2%80%99%20in%20exile%2C%20he%20could%20feel%20the%20pain%20of%20captivity%20and%20estrangement.%20With%20deep%20compassion%2C%20he%20would%20utter%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20home%20of%20youth%2C%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Etis%20far.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EOh!%20far%20away.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20hopes%20of%20youth%2C%20thy%E2%80%99ve%20fled%20and%20taught%20to%20weep%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20%E2%80%98Meghnadbadh%20Kabya%E2%80%99%2C%20his%20greatest%20gift%20to%20Indian%20literature%20that%20he%20would%20pen%20down%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20reflects%20similar%20ideas.%20He%20indeed%20criticised%20the%20assassination%20of%20Meghnad%2C%20the%20prince%20of%20Lanka%2C%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20Lakshmana%2C%20thus%20questioning%20the%20age-old%20tradition%20of%20portrayal%20of%20these%20figures%20as%20Gods.%20Under%20the%20outer%20skin%20of%20Ravana%20and%20Meghnad%E2%80%99s%20portrayal%20as%20tragic%20heroes%20and%20Rama%E2%80%99s%20portrayal%20as%20an%20anti-hero%20and%20a%20warrior%20who%20breaks%20the%20rules%20of%20war%20by%20taking%20the%20advantage%20of%20being%20closer%20to%20Gods%2C%20lies%20Madhusudan%E2%80%99s%20deep%20commentary%20of%20humanity.%20Rama%E2%80%99s%20concern%20for%20his%20beloved%20brother%20while%20sending%20him%20to%20the%20enemy%20camp%20to%20complete%20the%20daunting%20task%20of%20slaying%20Meghnad%2C%20Meghnad%20showing%20hospitality%20to%20Lakshmana%20even%20after%20he%20sneaked%20into%20the%20place%20of%20worship%2C%20Sita%E2%80%99s%20mourning%20over%20Meghnad%E2%80%99s%20untimely%20demise%2C%20a%20grief-stricken%20Ravana%20going%20out%20to%20war%2C%20Rama%E2%80%99s%20generosity%20in%20accepting%20a%20proposal%20of%20ceasefire%20during%20the%20seven-day%20mourning%20of%20Meghnad%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20all%20these%20events%20contribute%20to%20that%20concept%20of%20humanism%2C%20something%20which%20Dutta%20had%20embraced%20all%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20compared%20to%20his%20poems%2C%20verses%20and%20plays%2C%20his%20essays%2C%20which%20are%20personal%20favourites%2C%20haven%E2%80%99t%20received%20much%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20these%20essays%20were%20written%20in%20Madras.%20Reading%20his%20%E2%80%98Native%20Education%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Anglo-Saxon%20and%20the%20Hindu%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Mussalmans%20in%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Remarriage%20of%20Hindu%20Widows%E2%80%99%2C%20etc.%2C%20one%20can%20understand%20the%20direction%20of%20his%20opinion%20on%20contemporary%20political%20events.%20Over%2090%20years%20had%20already%20passed%20since%20the%20Battle%20of%20Plassey%2C%20and%20there%20were%20growing%20tensions%20between%20the%20Europeans%20and%20the%20native%20educated%20class%20in%20the%20big%20cities.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20Madhusudan%20always%20sided%20with%20the%20rationalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20essays%20written%20during%20this%20period%20also%20witnessed%20a%20transformation%20of%20language.%20He%20was%20no%20more%20the%20dreamy%20son%20of%20a%20wealthy%20father%20in%20Calcutta%2C%20but%20a%20man%20with%20responsibilities%2C%20struggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20It%20certainly%20influenced%20the%20tenor%20of%20his%20writing.%20Now%2C%20he%20was%20more%20direct%20and%20communicative%2C%20and%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20analytical%20and%20bold%20in%20his%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20composing%20essays%20on%20social%20themes%2C%20he%20would%20take%20a%20more%20radical%20path.%20That%20was%20natural%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20as%20a%20representative%20of%20the%20enlightened%20elite%20of%20the%2019th%20century%20Calcutta.%20As%20historian%20Sajal%20Nag%20has%20pointed%20out%2C%20of%20the%20three%20major%20currents%20of%20the%2019th%20century%20Bengal%20Renaissance%2C%20Rammohan%20Roy%20led%20the%20reformative%20movement%2C%20which%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20radicalism%20of%20Henry%20Louis%20Vivian%20Derozio%20(who%2C%20as%20a%20young%20teacher%20at%20Hindu%20College%2C%20used%20to%20engage%20his%20students%20in%20debates%20on%20various%20social%2C%20religious%20and%20political%20issues%2C%20and%20ask%20them%20to%20think%20freely%20and%20question%20everything)%20and%20the%20revivalism%20of%20Shree%20Ramkrishna%20Paramhansa.%20Madhusudan%20belonged%20to%20the%20second%20faction.%20A%20devoted%20Derozian%2C%20he%20was%20a%20man%20of%20reasons%20and%20even%20led%20an%20Anglicised%20lifestyle.%20But%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20his%20liberal%20contemporaries%20who%20were%20loudly%20critical%20of%20Hindu%20conservatism%20and%20inhumane%20practices%20but%20not%20of%20colonial%20exploitation%2C%20Madhusudan%20questioned%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20western-enlightened%20youth%2C%20he%20admitted%20the%20Anglo-Saxon%20race%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98well-graced%2C%20ravishing%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20audience%20with%20his%20manly%20beauty%E2%80%99%2C%20while%20the%20Hindu%20race%2C%20%E2%80%98once%E2%80%93a%20green%2C%20a%20beautiful%2C%20a%20tall%2C%20a%20majestical%2C%20a%20flowering%20tree%E2%80%99%2C%20was%20now%20%E2%80%98ill-favoured%2C%20worn%20out%20by%20the%20ceaseless%20waves%20of%20time%2C%20hoarse%20and%20dissonant%20as%20an%20untuned%20harp%2C%20as%20an%20unstrung%20lute.%E2%80%99%20These%20words%20may%20lead%20the%20readers%20to%20believe%20that%20his%20conversion%20made%20him%20an%20anti-Hindu.%20But%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20he%20was%20never%20a%20practising%20Christian.%20He%20even%20expressed%20his%20discontent%20in%20a%20few%20of%20his%20letters%20to%20his%20close%20friend%20Gourdas%20Basak%20when%20the%20latter%20started%20addressing%20him%20as%20%E2%80%98Christian%20Friend%20M.%E2%80%99%20To%20his%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20he%20always%20wanted%20to%20remain%20Madhu%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDuttakulodbhab%20%3C%2Fem%3E(one%20who%20is%20from%20Dutta%20family).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Madras%2C%20when%20he%20was%20working%20in%20a%20missionary-run%20institution%2C%20he%20lacked%20no%20courage%20in%20making%20a%20statement%20like%3A%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20under%20the%20Moslem%20rule%20was%20more%20prosperous%20than%20the%20Leadenhall%20rule.%20Sir%20Charles%20may%20disguise%20the%20fact%2C%20but%20history%20is%20against%20him.%E2%80%9D%20(Mussalmans%20in%20India)%20%E2%80%98Leadenhall%E2%80%99%20refers%20to%20the%20street%20in%20London%20where%20East%20India%20House%20was%20located.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20essay%20was%20subject%20to%20harsh%20criticism%2C%20as%20expected.%20Surprisingly%2C%20no%20one%20pointed%20to%20what%20he%20said%20about%20the%20extravagant%20lifestyles%20of%20the%20Nawabs%20and%20the%20Mughals%20of%20that%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20that%20was%20Madhusudan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20short-lived%20iconoclast%20(he%20was%20only%2049%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20death)%2C%20he%20never%20surrendered%20to%20any%20establishment.%20A%20visionary%20modernist%2C%20he%20only%20borrowed%20the%20best%20elements%20of%20the%20cultures%20he%20came%20across.%20A%20penniless%20genius%2C%20his%20creations%20had%20always%20been%20rich%20with%20opulence.%20And%2C%20as%20a%20staunch%20non-religious%20person%2C%20the%20only%20religion%20he%20ever%20preached%20was%20the%20religion%20of%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJanuary%2025%2C%202024%2C%20marked%20the%20bicentennial%20celebration%20of%20the%20200th%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20Michael%20Madhusudan%20Dutta.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESoham%20Das%20is%20a%20Kolkata-based%20freelance%20writer%20and%20researcher.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706959817000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03164144%2Fimage-1807.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fmichael-madhusudan-dutta-the-19th-century-poet-essayist-and-iconoclast%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22