%80%99%3A%20Taika%20Waititi%E2%80%99s%20Brand%20of%20Whimsy%20Produces%20a%20Tired%20and%20Saccharine%20Hollywood%20Product%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03142153%2Fimage-1804.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Brett%20and%20Steve%20Jamison%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ENext%20Goal%20Wins%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2014)%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cworst%20football%20team%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%9D%20held%20a%20few%20surprises.%20Charting%20the%20journey%20of%20the%20American%20Samoa%20national%20team%2C%20which%20was%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20FIFA%20ranking%20and%20searching%20for%20a%20win%20for%20almost%20a%20decade%20after%20infamously%20losing%2031-0%20to%20Australia%20in%202001%2C%20the%20documentary%20became%20a%20touching%20ode%20to%20the%20strivers%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20underdog%20films%20end%20with%20winning%2C%20but%20the%20stakes%20here%20were%20significantly%20lower.%20The%20president%20of%20the%20Football%20Federation%20of%20American%20Samoa%20(or%20FFAS)%20keeps%20telling%20his%20players%20that%20he%20wants%20to%20see%20them%20score%20just%20one%20goal.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20do%20one%E2%80%99s%20best%20rather%20than%20necessarily%20win%2C%20an%20interesting%20thought%20for%20a%20sports%20film.%20And%20to%20do%20this%2C%20they%20hire%20Thomas%20Rongen%2C%20of%20Dutch%20origin%20but%20based%20largely%20in%20America.%20Like%20any%20other%20fish-out-of-water%20story%2C%20Rongen%20resents%20the%20assignment%20at%20first%2C%20but%20later%20comes%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20warmth%20of%20the%20local%20community%20and%20the%20unspoken%20spirit%20of%20his%20team.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20story%20that%20could%20stir%20even%20the%20most%20cynical%20among%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20premise%20almost%20feels%20handmade%20for%20someone%20like%20Taika%20Waititi%2C%20known%20for%20his%20earnest%20films%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EJojo%20Rabbit%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20with%20plenty%20of%20quirk.%20Like%20he%20does%20in%20most%20of%20his%20films%2C%20Waititi%20appears%20in%20this%20feature%20film%20adaptation%20of%20the%202014%20documentary%2C%20warning%20us%20he%E2%80%99ll%20tell%20the%20story%20with%20few%20embellishments.%20Like%20in%20most%20of%20his%20work%2C%20the%20pitch%20of%20Waititi%E2%80%99s%20adaptation%20is%20decidedly%20silly%20and%20jovial.%20The%20film%20characterises%20the%20American%20Samoans%20as%20a%20happy%2C%20self-sufficient%20community%2C%20while%20Rongen%20(played%20by%20Michael%20Fassbender)%20is%20the%20grumpy%20mainlander%2C%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20wrap%20his%20head%20around%20why%20his%20team%20is%20so%20laid%20back%20even%20after%20facing%20defeat%20so%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWaititi%E2%80%99s%20sketch-writing%20ability%20is%20never%20in%20question%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20one%20of%20the%20best%20in%20the%20business.%20Like%20in%20the%20first%20scene%20where%20we%20meet%20Rongen%2C%20where%20he%E2%80%99s%20being%20fired%20from%20his%20current%20employment%2C%20with%20the%20only%20option%20being%20to%20coach%20the%20American%20Samoan%20football%20team.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20a%20version%20of%20this%20in%20many%20films%2C%20but%20what%20elevates%20it%20is%20the%20humour%20in%20it%20by%20director%20Waititi%20and%20co-writer%20Iain%20Morris.%20As%20Rongen%20tries%20to%20persuade%20the%20panel%20to%20change%20their%20decision%2C%20we%20hear%20a%20presentation%20about%20the%20five%20stages%20of%20grief.%20Similarly%2C%20we%20see%20the%20character%20of%20Ace%20(David%20Fane)%20as%20the%20outrageously%20even-tempered%20local%20coach%2C%20who%20%E2%80%9Chates%E2%80%9D%20pressure.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20low-hanging%20fruit%20of%20a%20character%2C%20but%20Fane%20acts%20so%20beautifully%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20impossible%20to%20resist%20his%20charms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFassbender%2C%20who%20came%20out%20of%20his%20acting%20sabbatical%20only%20a%20few%20months%20ago%20in%20David%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2023)%2C%20is%20in%20good%20form.%20His%20first%20words%20on%20the%20island%20are%20Liam%20Neeson%E2%80%99s%20legendary%20monologue%20from%20%3Cem%3ETaken%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2008).%20However%2C%20you%20do%20get%20a%20sense%20that%20Rongen%E2%80%99s%20character%20might%20have%20made%20more%20of%20an%20impact%20as%20a%20supporting%20character.%20It%E2%80%99s%20understandable%20that%20for%20a%20studio%20to%20back%20a%20project%20with%20a%20primary%20cast%20filled%20with%20American%20Samoan%20actors%2C%20they%20would%20insist%20on%20a%20recognisable%20face.%20Fassbender%20is%20more%20than%20competent%20at%20playing%20the%20fool%20here%2C%20but%20there%E2%80%99s%20only%20so%20much%20you%20can%20do%20to%20reinvent%20the%20bitter%2C%20alcoholic%20coach%20with%20rage%20issues.%20No%20one%20from%20the%20team%2C%20especially%20Rongen%E2%80%99s%20evolving%20dynamic%20with%20them%2C%20gets%20anything%20particularly%20memorable%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20character%20of%20Jaiyah%20(Kaimana)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20trans%20player%20on%20the%20team.%20She%20is%20one%20of%20the%20quieter%2C%20almost%20incidental%20portions%20in%20the%202014%20documentary%2C%20but%20over%20here%20Waititi%20and%20Morris%20bring%20her%20front-and-centre%2C%20to%20slap%20us%20with%20their%20progressive%20values.%20There%E2%80%99s%20an%20unnecessary%20scene%20when%20Rongen%20bullies%20her%2C%20by%20calling%20her%20by%20her%20dead%20name.%20It%E2%80%99s%20such%20an%20unsubtle%20writing%20device%20to%20make%20sure%20Rongen%20and%20Jaiyah%20come%20around%20after%20that%20moment%20of%20brief%20conflict%2C%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%20shocking.%20Then%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20meta-commentary%20of%20Rongen%20watching%20Al%20Pacino%E2%80%99s%20fiery%20monologue%20from%20%3Cem%3EAny%20Given%20Sunday%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1999)%20on%20the%20night%20before%20a%20match%2C%20amusing%20at%20first%2C%20but%20also%20hinting%20at%20the%20fatigue%20around%20the%20locker-room%20monologues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20ephemeral%20impact%20of%20Waititi%E2%80%99s%20choices%2C%20there%20are%20two%20moments%20that%20really%20hit%20home.%20One%20where%20Rongen%20shows%20he%20trusts%20his%20team%20by%20telling%20them%20about%20his%20grief.%20What%20could%20have%20been%20a%20sappy%20scene%20otherwise%2C%20Fassbender%20lifts%20up%20by%20being%20heartbreakingly%20sincere.%20Another%20is%20when%20Gail%20(Elisabeth%20Moss)%2C%20Rongen%E2%80%99s%20icy%20ex-wife%2C%20calls%20him%20for%20a%20night-cap%2C%20and%20completely%20changes%20our%20perception%20from%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20two%20adequate%20scenes%20and%20a%20few%20jokes%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20a%20summer.%20Waititi%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ENext%20Goal%20Wins%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebarely%20lives%20up%20to%20being%20a%20crowd-pleaser%20in%20the%20end.%20To%20take%20a%20documentary%20that%20flipped%20the%20underdog%20sports%20drama%20template%2C%20and%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20warm%2C%20saccharine%20Hollywood%20product%20feels%20like%20a%20disservice.%20I%E2%80%99d%20be%20up%20for%20Taika%20Waititi%E2%80%99s%20whimsy%20on%20most%20days%2C%20but%20only%20if%20it%20had%20some%20insight%20to%20go%20with%20it.%20It%E2%80%99s%20true%20that%20you%20miss%20100%25%20of%20the%20shots%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20take%2C%20but%20adaptations%20like%20these%20are%20simply%20not%20worth%20the%20effort.%20I%E2%80%99d%20rather%20go%20watch%20reruns%20of%20(the%20first%20two%20seasons%20of)%20%3Cem%3ETed%20Lasso%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706954433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03142153%2Fimage-1804.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fnext-goal-wins-taika-waititis-brand-of-whimsy-produces-a-tired-and-saccharine-hollywood-product%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20feature%20film%20of%20the%202014%20documentary%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Cworst%20football%20team%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%9D%20fails%20to%20score%20on%20many%20counts%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fnext-goal-wins-taika-waititis-brand-of-whimsy-produces-a-tired-and-saccharine-hollywood-product%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ED%20to%20probe%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20if%20charges%20of%20fund%20siphoning%20found%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706953286000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-06%2F21%2Ffull%2F1687319075-8743.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-to-probe-paytm-payments-bank-if-charges-of-fund-siphoning-found-124020300453_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20(RBI)%20on%20Wednesday%20ordered%20the%20payments%20bank%20unit%20of%20One%2097%20Communications%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20Paytm%2C%20to%20stop%20accepting%20fresh%20deposits%20in%20its%20accounts%20or%20popular%20wallets%20from%20March%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-to-probe-paytm-payments-bank-if-charges-of-fund-siphoning-found-124020300453_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-to-probe-paytm-payments-bank-if-charges-of-fund-siphoning-found-124020300453_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-to-probe-paytm-payments-bank-if-charges-of-fund-siphoning-found-124020300453_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%2014%20Lakh%20New%20Cancer%20Cases%20and%209%20Lakh%20Deaths%20in%20India%20in%202022%3A%20WHO%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03134915%2Fimage-1802.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20reported%20more%20than%2014%20lakh%20new%20cancer%20cases%20and%20over%209%20lakh%20deaths%20due%20to%20the%20disease%20in%202022%2C%20said%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Agency%20for%20Research%20on%20Cancer%20(IARC)%2C%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20cancer%20arm%2C%20unveiled%20a%20report%20highlighting%20the%20prevalence%20and%20patterns%20of%20cancer%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20Indian%20women%2C%20breast%20and%20cervix%20cancers%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20common%2C%20constituting%20nearly%2027%25%20and%2018%25%20of%20new%20cases%2C%20respectively%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fnation%2F2024%2FFeb%2F02%2Fover-14-lakh-new-cancer-cases-nine-lakh-deaths-in-india-in-2022-breast-cancer-most-common-among-women%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20men%2C%20lip%20and%20oral%20cavity%20cancers%20and%20lung%20cancers%20took%20the%20lead%2C%20making%20up%2015.6%25%20and%208.5%25%20of%20new%20cases%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IARC%20report.%20The%20report%20also%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20survival%20rates%2C%20revealing%20that%20nearly%2032.6%20lakh%20people%20in%20India%20were%20alive%20within%20five%20years%20of%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWHO%20made%20a%20dire%20prediction%2C%20anticipating%20a%2077%25%20surge%20in%20new%20cancer%20cases%20to%20over%2035%20million%20by%202050%2C%20with%20deaths%20nearly%20doubling%20from%202012%20to%20exceed%2018%20million.%20Key%20factors%20contributing%20to%20this%20alarming%20trend%20included%20tobacco%20use%2C%20alcohol%20consumption%2C%20obesity%2C%20population%20aging%2C%20and%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20cancer%20before%20the%20age%20of%2075%20was%20calculated%20at%2010.6%25%2C%20while%20the%20risk%20of%20succumbing%20to%20cancer%20by%20the%20same%20age%20stood%20at%207.2%25.%20On%20a%20global%20scale%2C%20these%20risks%20were%20significantly%20higher%20at%2020%25%20and%209.6%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELung%20cancer%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20common%20cancer%2C%20accounting%20for%2012.4%25%20of%20new%20cases%20and%20nearly%2019%25%20of%20total%20cancer%20deaths.%20Breast%20cancer%20followed%20closely%20as%20the%20second%20most%20common%2C%20contributing%20to%2011.6%25%20of%20total%20new%20cases%20and%207%25%20of%20global%20cancer%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECervical%20cancer%2C%20although%20the%20eighth%20most%20commonly%20occurring%20globally%2C%20ranked%20ninth%20in%20causing%20cancer-related%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20prevalence%2C%20the%20IARC%20expressed%20optimism%20about%20the%20potential%20elimination%20of%20cervical%20cancer%20as%20a%20public%20health%20problem%20through%20the%20WHO%20Cervical%20Cancer%20Elimination%20Initiative.%20This%20initiative%2C%20urging%20countries%20to%20maintain%20an%20incidence%20rate%20below%204%20per%201%20lakh%20women%2C%20emphasised%20key%20strategies%20such%20as%20HPV%20vaccination%2C%20regular%20screenings%2C%20and%20efficient%20treatment%20protocols.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20interim%20budget%2C%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20announced%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20push%20for%20cervical%20cancer%20vaccination%20for%20girls%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of%209%20to%2014%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706952623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F03134915%2Fimage-1802.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fover-14-lakh-new-cancer-cases-and-9-lakh-deaths-in-india-in-2022-who%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Among%20Indian%20women%2C%20breast%20and%20cervix%20cancers%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20common%2C%20constituting%20nearly%2027%25%20and%2018%25%20of%20new%20cases%2C%20respectively.%20For%20men%2C%20lip%20and%20oral%20cavity%20cancers%20and%20lung%20cancers%20took%20the%20lead%2C%20making%20up%2015.6%25%20and%20